  "description": "Wendy Brown (1955–) is an American political theorist whose work analyzes the conditions under which liberal-democratic political life has been hollowed out — by neoliberal rationality, by the politicization of injury, by the rise of authoritarian formations from inside ostensibly democratic states.",
